glosses: to solve, resolve, decipher, figure out, reason

etymology: From Ottoman Turkish چوزمك (çözmek, “to untie, unfasten, loosen, unravel, solve”), from Proto-Turkic [Term?]. Cognate with Karakhanid [script needed] (çöžmēk, “to pull, stretch”), Azerbaijani çözmək (“to resolve”), Chagatai [script needed] (çözmek, “to take off, pull off, disperse”), Khorezmian Turkic [script needed] (çöz-, “to loosen, untie”), Kipchak [Arabic needed] (çöz-, “to untwist, untie”), Turkmen çözmek (“to untie, unleash, solve”).
